A strong presence of Italian publishers at the Frankfurt International Book Fair.
More than three hundred Italian publishers attended the 60th edition of the Buchmesse, the most important international rights-exchange event.
The Frankfurt International Book Fair is expected to attract more than 7 000 exhibitors from 101 countries, occupying the 171.790 square metres of the fair with over 403 000 titles on display, and Turkey as the guest of honour.
The Italian Government will be represented by Francesco Maria Giro, Undersecretary of the Ministry of Cultural Affairs and Heritage, at the opening ceremony of the Italian Butterfly.
